reviews.review_text: ahh 74 jerry if you're on a slobber-fest over these 1974 recordings, like i am !, download this! not as clear as Jerry's other recordings, but it's one of those that puts you right down on the floor ! these are national treasures! thankyouthankyouthankyou!!!

Mellow 1974 I was concerened about something on the way into work today..now I can't remember..Thank God for the GRATEFUL DEAD !!! now the review...

Black throated wind...mellow keyboard tones..soooo '74...

(Heard a "Queen Jane" from London 1990 show on GD Channel last night & said to self "I like Hornsby and the 2 keyboard thang but he is way too loud on this mix".. Compare that to the keyboards in this show this .no comparison..totally different animal)
BTW...whew...so meloow..makes you feel like a stoned hitchiker
Peggy-O: Slow..mellow again..beautiful keyboards

If I was able to in 1974..I'd be packin' up the VW Camper just to bathe my soul in the light that is the beauty of 1974 Dead.

Jack Straw..Still heavenly keyboards

Loser..don't you push me babeee..5 stars for the fatman's vocals..Jerrys guitar from 4:00 - 4:38  is clean and schools everyother guitoarist from 74...
GSET...I even like loud Bobby ! The peaks and valleys are sweet.."can't close the door when the walls caved in.." preach it Bobby

Cumberland..again killer keyboards throughout..check out jerry vs keith at 4:15 - 5:00

PITB>UJB>PITB..MONSTER ..EPIC..BIBLICAL...'nuff said..gettin weird @ 17:00
CHINA CAT>RIDER..Monster 28:00 + breakin down then brining it home...
Scarlet Begonias Ok show, down a notch from '73.
